Big Tech earnings: The 3 things Wall Street will be listening for
content.description:
Big Tech is on deck for earnings season this week with Magnificent Seven companies Meta Platforms (META), Microsoft (MSFT), and Alphabet (GOOGL, GOOG) reporting quarterly results on Wednesday, and Amazon (AMZN) and Apple (AAPL) publishing their releases on Thursday.

Yahoo Finance senior reporters Ines Ferré and Allie Canal and Washington Crossing Advisors Senior Portfolio Manager Chad Morganlander explain what they will be watching from these Big Tech names, including Amazon's reaction to its massive AWS outage last week, AI capex spending, and Apple's (AAPL) integration of artificial intelligence into devices.

To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.

content.description: Policymakers at the Federal Reserve will deliver a 25 basis point rate cut on Wednesday according to Anna Macdonald from Aubrey Asset Management. She warned that markets should be aware of the lack of data due to the government shutdown and the impact this could have on future rate decision. Five of the Magnificent Seven stocks report this week and she has high expectations. She also believes investors should focus on what they have to say on AI.

content.description:
Beyond Meat (BYND) rallied by 1,300% over the course of several sessions last week, igniting a new meme stock trading frenzy.
